The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Death ride on taxi
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Death ride on taxi
          TAPAS CHAKRABORTY                              
	Lucknow, Nov. 28: Mohammad Omar drove a couple of men in his taxi on Wednesday night. In addition to the fare, they gave him death.        
	The duo  part of the gang who unleashed terror on Mumbai  had left behind a grenade in his taxi.        
	The 27-year-old from Siddharthnagar district in Uttar Pradesh was among the north Indian migrants targeted by Raj Thackerays Maharashtra Navnirman Sena, his father said Abdul Khaleq said today.         
	When he came home during Diwali, he told us he was scared. Now suddenly, how did he become an enemy of the jihadis?        
	Omars body was identified by his brother-in-law Mohammad Ershad who lives in Mumbai. He reached Dafalpurwa village in Siddharthnagar last night to convey the news to his family of four  Omar has a brother and a sister.        
	On Wednesday, the two terrorists flagged down Omars vehicle at Vile Parle, police said. They got off after a while. Within minutes, the grenade blew up.         
	The incident took place around 9.30pm, making Omar one of the earlier victims of the terror attacks.        
	Omars mother Kuflan Bibi fainted several times since being told of her sons death. He had promised to take her to Mumbai in January.        
	The family owns three acres of land, but it is not enough. We wait for my brothers money order. That is what gives us bread and medicines for my parents, Omars brother Shahid, 21, said.                                                                                                                                                                          
